scinated view of power, frequently citing the inevitability of corruption and the "brainrot" of modern economies, while simultaneously praising the "indomitable human spirit." There is a notable lean toward conspiratorial or "alternative" historical narratives, evidenced by their focus on the Rothschilds, the "Jewish and Arab" influence on global systems, and the clandestine activities of the CIA or Freemasons. Ultimately, Divini appears to be a seeker of synthesis, attempting to reconcile the "uncanny suffering" of biological existence with a hopeful, almost romanticized vision of technological innovation and urban planning.	2025-12-30 13:53:15.895693+00	108
